COYOTE RIDGE WIND, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Coyote Ridge Wind, LLC ("Coyote Ridge") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from a wind generating facility located in Brookings County, South Dakota. Coyote Ridge is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Northern States Power Company under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Coyote Ridge's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Coyote Ridge facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Coyote Ridge's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Coyote Ridge shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission, Energy and Operating Reserve Markets Tariff.
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
Total Revenue Requirement:
The Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement is: $0.00 for the period January 1, 2022 - January 31, 2022 and $363,000.00, effective February 1, 2022 The Monthly Revenue Requirement is: $0.00 for the period January 1, 2022 - January 31, 2022; and $30,250.00 effective February 1, 2022 (Based on Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement divided by 12)
